# Whitelist-only pattern for the hive-mind hub (v0.3.0+). Default-ignore
# everything, allow only the canonical hub schema. Written to
# $HIVE_MIND_HUB_DIR/.gitignore by setup.sh at hub install time.

/*

!/.gitignore
!/.gitattributes
!/.hive-mind-format

# Global canonical content (provider-agnostic; maps to CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, etc.).
!/content.md

# Per-project canonical memory tree. The whitelist is a catch-all
# because project-ids are normalized git remotes and ROUTINELY contain
# slashes (`github.com/owner/repo` = 3 levels; self-hosted forges may
# go deeper). The earlier single-level patterns (`/projects/*/memory.md`,
# `/projects/*/memory/**`) silently blocked every multi-level id from
# reaching the remote — harvest copied the file into the hub working
# tree but `git add -A` skipped it, and the canonical per-project
# memory never synced across machines. Trust harvest to have already
# filtered what lands here (tool-side session transcripts, auth
# files, etc. never get mapped in ADAPTER_PROJECT_CONTENT_RULES); the
# secret-file gate in core/hub/sync.sh catches any misconfigured
# harvest that sneaks a declared-secret basename into projects/**.
!/projects/
!/projects/**

# User-level skills, provider-agnostic.
!/skills/
!/skills/**

# Hermes (Nous Research hermes-agent) blob mirror. Hermes does not
# participate in the shared `content.md` tier; its whole tool dir is
# mirrored verbatim. The adapter's blob mirror also carries the tool's
# own `.gitignore`, so anything Hermes itself wants ignored (cache/,
# logs/, .env, ...) is filtered at this layer too.
!/hermes/
!/hermes/**

# Canonical config: reserved env vars.
!/config/
!/config/env.sh

# Mac clutter.
**/.DS_Store

# Everything below this line stays machine-local and must NEVER be
# pushed: the hive-mind source clone, the symlinked sync entry point,
# lock / rate-limit state, error logs.
/hive-mind/
/bin/
/.install-state/
/.hive-mind-state/
/.sync-error.log
